docs.snippet: Business in the foreign exchange market last week was beset by financial and political developments in Europe. The fall of the Belgian Cabinet and the delay in re-forming a new one, also the strained European relations provoked by Germany's...
docs.lead_paragraph: Business in the foreign exchange market last week was beset by financial and political developments in Europe. The fall of the Belgian Cabinet and the delay in re-forming a new one, also the strained European relations provoked by Germany's re-establishment of obligatory military, service were regarded as the reasons for the irregularity. As a result, a nervous tension underlie the trading, bringing sharp fluctuations in all currencies.
